                            <img src="https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/EB096218-ED23-E8AF-49E048261B1677DF.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="The Blue Onion Dome of the Armory and the spire of the Church against a cloudy blue sky." title="The Blue Onion Dome was rebuilt after the fire in February of 1864. Today it graces the skyline of Hartford, just as the the Church of the Good Shepherd does, reminding those who see if of the Colts and their legacy." />
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>The Blue Onion Dome was rebuilt after the fire in February of 1864. Today it graces the skyline of Hartford, just as the the Church of the Good Shepherd does, reminding those who see if of the Colts and their legacy.</p>
