                                <h3 class="card-title">The Church of the Good Shepherd</h3>
                            </div>
                            <img src="https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/EB2CF528-E321-D96B-CD91D782D29281DE.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="A church and trees against the backdrop of a bight blue sky and clouds." title="The Church of the Good Shepherd was built by Elizabeth Colt as memorial to her husband, Samuel Colt, and their three children who passed in infancy. It was designed by Edward Tuckerman Potter and dedicate in 1869." />
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>The Church of the Good Shepherd was built by Elizabeth Colt as memorial to her husband, Samuel Colt, and their three children who passed in infancy. It was designed by Edward Tuckerman Potter and dedicate in 1869.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
